subSubSection.paragraph: Type locality: Tokyo fish market, probably from Shimonoseki, Japan .

The three Taiwanese samples of
S. brevirostris
included in this analysis formed a single cluster that included two samples of
S. brevirostris
from Japan (
Figure 4
). Until recently, this species was considered to be a junior synonym of
S. megalops
but molecular and morphological studies have shown this is a species complex. The S.

brevirostris
clade is sister to the
S. cf. megalops
clade that includes samples from off South Africa and Angola (
Figure 4
).
